The assessment objectives are the basis for your exams — you need to meet them to get top marks
1)You will need to show the examiner that you can meet the following :
shows an insightful, critical and engaged personal response to the text
supports arguments with well-integrated, highly relevant and precise examples from the text
closely and perceptively analyses in detail how the writer uses language, form and structure
to create meaning and affect the audience, using highly relevant subject terminology
gives a detailed, relevant explanation of the relationship between the text and its context
uses highly varied vocabulary and sentence types and accurate spelling and punctuation
shows a critical and observant personal response to the text
supports arguments with integrated, well-chosen examples from the text
includes a thorough exploration of how the writer uses language, form and structure
to create meaning and affect the audience, making use of appropriate subject terminology
explores the relationship between the text and its context
uses a wide range of vocabulary and sentence types and fairly accurate spelling and punctuation
shows a thoughtful and clear personal response to the text
examines how the writer uses language, form and structure to create meaning
and affect the audience, making some use of relevant subject terminology
uses a moderate range of vocabulary and sentence types, without
spelling and punctuation errors which make the meaning unclear
